# Repository layout — skills and symlinks

Edit agent skills only in `skills/`. These paths are symlinks to the same tree — do not treat them as separate copies:

- `.cursor/skills/` → `skills/`
- `.agents/skills/` → `skills/`

These external readmes are file symlinks — same content as the skill reference, not duplicates to diff or merge:

- `summary.md` → `skills/reatom/REFERENCE.md`
- `docs/src/content/docs/summary.md` → `skills/reatom/REFERENCE.md`
- `packages/core/README.md` → `skills/reatom/REFERENCE.md`
- `packages/jsx/README.md` → `skills/reatom-jsx/REFERENCE.md`

When updating API or JSX docs, edit the canonical file under `skills/`. Do not compare or sync symlink targets.

